Seven traders on Tuesday pleaded guilty to selling shisha and were fined Sh5,000 each. Imran Akhtar, Oliver Majimbo, Cindy Mugoya, Salma Sakwa, Vodambula Nelson, Marion Nanjala and Flora Masera appeared before Kibera chief magistrate Joyce Gandani. They were arrested on September 16 by officers on patrol after a tip-off from residents. Court documents say that they were arrested at Caf√© Deira, Westlands, in Nairobi county while selling 51 pipes of shisha and 10 assorted flavours. They asked the court for forgiveness. Chief magistrate Gandani fined them and ordered that the shisha containers be destroyed.